# Terminology Layers

HairAudit has two **user-visible** language layers. Internal code names (e.g. `AuditOS` in `src/lib/auditos/`) are fine; **never expose forbidden terms in UI, reports, emails, or i18n shown to patients**.

## Patient layer — never show

Do not use these words or phrases in patient-facing copy:

- AI
- GPT
- Forensic
- Intelligence Engine
- AuditOS
- Precision Score
- Surgical Intelligence
- Platinum Tier
- Gold Tier

**Applies to:** `src/components/patient/**`, `src/app/**/patient/**`, `src/app/dashboard/patient/**`, patient-safe summaries/reports, patient i18n keys, and any marketing or intake flow aimed at patients.

Use neutral, clinical language instead — e.g. "independent review", "case summary", "areas to discuss with your clinic".

```tsx
// ❌ BAD (patient dashboard)
<p>Powered by Forensic AI — Precision Score: 82</p>

// ✅ GOOD
<p>Your independent case review summary</p>
```

## Clinic / auditor layer — can show

These terms are allowed (and expected) in professional-facing UI:

- Forensic AI
- Graft Integrity Index
- Donor Density Analytics
- Extraction Pattern Review
- Surgical Intelligence
- Procedural Analytics

**Applies to:** `src/app/dashboard/clinic/**`, `src/app/dashboard/auditor/**`, `src/app/dashboard/doctor/**`, clinic/doctor audit forms, and professional report views.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD (auditor dashboard)
<h2>Extraction Pattern Review</h2>
<p>Forensic AI findings for this case</p>
```

## When editing i18n

- Check which audience a key serves before adding terms.
- Patient keys: scan for forbidden terms before merging.
- Clinic/auditor keys: professional terminology above is allowed.
